name: Hanif Abdurraqib
tweet: I can only speak for myself but a part of the reason I love the purchasing of albums now is because I'm still fascinated/excited by the physical object. I'm maybe only 10 years into comfortably (v key word) buying albums, despite living a life defined by/surrounded by music.

name: Hanif Abdurraqib
tweet: I don't know numbers or metrics but am merely saying that when I see talk about young people not buying music like they used to, it feels worthwhile to point out that some of us never really could. At least not at the level of some other folks.

name: Hanif Abdurraqib
tweet: I didn't buy a lot of music growing up (at all) because I had no money. A real gift of having older siblings/older heads who could get tapes and CDs was that I could afford (or find, or steal) blank tapes/CDs for recording easier that I could afford the albums.
